OL,3,CHealth issues won't be solved by one
OL,4,Cminister in one term, says Swann
OL,6,FThe pressures and delays facing NHS
OL,7,Fworkers and users has led to a
OL,8,Fperception that the health system is
OL,9,Fno longer working for everyone.
OL,11,FThe minister said that "at this point
OL,12,Fin time I would agree with that
OL,13,Fanalogy. It's not one I want
OL,15,F"I want a National Health Service free
OL,16,Fat the point of need. And I that's
OL,17,Fwhere we have to get back to so those
OL,18,Fwho need the service can actually
OL,19,Faccess it in the same timely manner as
OL,20,Fthose who want to pay.
