OL,3,CHealth issues won't be solved by one
OL,4,Cminister in one term, says Swann
OL,6,F"There always has to be an option, I
OL,7,Fbelieve, of that private sector. If
OL,8,Fsomebody wants to pay for health
OL,9,Ftreatment, they can get it.
OL,11,F"But they shouldn't be forced down
OL,12,Fthat route. There should be a National
OL,13,FHealth Service at the point of need
OL,14,Fand the point of delivery."
